	       Mogadishu - The director of an ambulance service in Mogadishu says 15 primary school children are among the over 300 people killed in Somalia's deadliest blast. Abdulkadir Adam told The Associated Press that the children were on a school bus died when the massive truck bomb detonated nearby. Saturday's attack struck a crowded street near some of Somalia's government ministries. About 300 people are injured, many of them badly.    24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  